From 5a1e10458e60fdeeed477e0f4b088c8edb77004c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
Date: Thu, 10 Apr 2025 23:26:47 +0530
Subject: [PATCH] mac80211: wifi cancel CAC process when leaving Mesh

When the mesh interface starts with a DFS channel (100),
mac80211 start the CAC worker process. If the mesh interface
is removeed and started with a non-DFS channel (like channel 36)
before CAC completion, the CAC worker continues running,
causing a crash in the mac80211 driver after CAC completion.

Cancel the DFS CAC worker in mac80211 when leaving
the mesh interface if cac_started is true

Signed-off-by: Ramasamy Kaliappan <quic_rkaliapp@quicinc.com>
Signed-off-by: Balamurugan Ramar <quic_bramar@quicinc.com>
---
 net/wireless/mesh.c | 5 ++++-
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/net/wireless/mesh.c b/net/wireless/mesh.c
index 2c66540..21a63d5 100644
--- a/net/wireless/mesh.c
+++ b/net/wireless/mesh.c
@@ -271,8 +271,11 @@ int cfg80211_leave_mesh(struct cfg80211_registered_device *rdev,
 	if (!rdev->ops->leave_mesh)
 		return -EOPNOTSUPP;
 
-	if (!wdev->u.mesh.id_len)
+	if (!wdev->u.mesh.id_len) {
+		if (wdev->links[0].cac_started)
+			rdev_end_cac(rdev, wdev->netdev, 0);
 		return -ENOTCONN;
+	}
 
 	err = rdev_leave_mesh(rdev, dev);
 	if (!err) {
-- 
2.34.1

